5:
Yep, that's me, happy with just being
friends forever! Well, if HE comes on
to me first, that's another story. I'd
pounce.
7:
I guess I'll just keep him around.
Nothing like having a convenient
backup boy in your pocket.
14:
Backup... boy... No! No, no, no! That's
not true!
17:
But... What if he does... What if he
were to...
24:
The city really is beautiful at night.
Though not nearly as beautiful as
you.
29:
I'm your operator, Nate. I tell you
what to do. I thought you liked it that
way?
34:
W-we have to do this properly.
These things have an order to them,
you know!
37:
You... You have to say it first. Tell me
that you love me.
45:
Nooo! That's... all wrong! That's not
Alk at all!
50:
Hey, Nate. I was thinking of how to
pay you back for those chocolates...
I thought of something.
62:
I've really caught the love bug,
haven't I? I can't stop thinking
about... you know.
66:
Why the sudden change?! Did
something happen?
70:
Y-yes, but... Sorry, you're THE last
person I'm going to tell. Still, can I
ask for your advice anyway?
74:
You want me to give you advice
without knowing what even
happened? Oookay then.
78:
You know what it probably is? I'm
just a simple-minded girl who's
easily distracted by a pretty face!
That's it!
81:
I guess I should test this out. Themis,
could you come over here?
86:
You really are the worst, teasing me
like that. But fine, I'll play along.
90: I'll give you everything I've got.
94:
Obscene acts in violation of public
policy will be dealt with by our
arbiter over there, so don't get too
close or anything!
98:
How naive of you, Nate. You should
know adults have other ways of
getting what they want.
101:
Say, do you want to come over to
my place and look at some of my
master's official merch? There's
some premium stuff in there.
110:
Hook, line, and sinker huh? As
arbiter, I'm gonna step in here and
say this simulation's over.
115:
What? No, it wasn't 'cause of the
merch! My heart did kind of skip a
beat when I saw her face up close,
though.
120:
I hope you learned something from
that. Imagine what would have
happened if it was someone else
who pulled that trick on you.
125:
By the way, Themis... What were you
planning on doing if she actually
went home with you?
134:
And Nate, you really need to learn to
be more cautious!
139:
I... do? Am I really so easily won over
by a pretty face?
145:
Let's turn that frown upside down,
Hero! There's work to be done, and it
won't wait for you to stop moping
around!
148:
Two troubleshooters are stirring up
some... well, trouble on the street. It's
a big ruckus. Apparently, it's
because—
153:
Okay, wait! So it IS true that I
cheated on you, but... I only did it to
make myself realize how much I
love YOU!
155:
Liar! No good, dirty, rotten, lying
son-of-a... You're just an idiot who
falls for any pretty face he sees!
158:
That line sounds familiar, doesn't it,
Nate?
162:
It's not like she's specifically talking
about me!
165:
It doesn't matter! If I can't have the
love of my life, no one will! Time to
DIE, darling!
167:
You there—stay out of this! This has
nothing to do with you!
170:
You're trying to kill each other in the
middle of the street. It very much
has something to do with me!
173:
This is just the same old stuff as
always—I've solved hundreds of
squabbles between jealous lovers
this month alone!
176:
No! This is different! He... that
bastard betrayed me, and the only
way he'll make up for it is BY DYING!
178:
I didn't betray you! I was just... trying
out other merchandise! You know,
seeing what was out there!
181:
How have you not already been
stabbed and left in a ditch
somewhere?
184:
Think about it! If I'm with an even
prettier gal than you, and I don't feel
anything, that's just proof of how
much I love YOU!
186:
"Don't feel anything," my ass! You
could just skip the step where you
cheat on me, you miserable
bastard! DIE ALREADY!
189:
I'm not even sure I follow anymore,
but, uh... How about we all just calm
down?
192:
Alright then, "Hero," since you refuse
to shut up and leave us alone, tell
me... Who do YOU think is right?
198:
Whatever his stupid reasons were,
the fact remains that he cheated on
me!
200:
Now hold on! Think about stories:
you can read one and "feel"
something, but it's not actually real,
right?
202:
Cheating's the same! Even if you
happen to "feel" something ONE
time, that doesn't make it real!
What's real is my love for YOU!
204:
Then why not just download some
emotions directly to your drive?
Surely there's no need to ACTUALLY
CHEAT!
206:
No, no! I can't download someone
else's emotions—they have to be
MINE! Otherwise, I can't compare
them properly!
210: No—it's TRUE LOVE, is what it is!
216:
How the hell am I supposed to
know?!
223:
Yeah, this is pretty much impossible.
For me, at least.
227:
Man, you couldn't make up a
situation that crazy if you tried.
230:
If I were to download their emotions,
I'd probably puke. I'd rather get
nerve surgery again than do that.
234:
Y-yikes... That sounds like it was
really intense.
238:
I don't think I have it in me to
process emotions that intense. Not
right now, anyway.
241:
I've got so many things I need to
do... So many things I want to do!
There's no time left for figuring out
"love"!
245:
I kind of get where you're coming
from.
250:
So you know what? FORGET love! I'm
done with it! That's it, end of story!
Let's eat.
253:
And, you know, it's 'cause you do
nice things like this that people get
the wrong idea. You've gotta keep
your guard up, Alk.
257:
I'm supposed to stop making food
for people now?!
